Turmeric in combination with red chillies help make Thai Yellow different from the other colours of curry in Thai cuisine, resulting in a milder sauce. Here, our Thai Yellow Style Veggie Noodle Soup heroes the veg.

== Prep ==

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Trim the @pak choi{1}, then thinly slice widthways. Halve the @tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} widthways.

Zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

== Cooking the Noodles and Broccoli ==

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to the boil.

When boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{125%g} and broccoli. Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another large saucepan on medium-high heat. Drain the @king prawns{150%g}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns.

== Making the Soup ==

Once the oil is hot, add the prawns. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and stir-fry for ~{4-5%minutes}. Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Add the @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @yellow Thai style paste{45%g}. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @peanut butter{30%g} and @coconut milk{180%ml}. Mix well until combined.

Add in the @sugar{1%tsp} and @water for the soup{150%ml}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and stir until everything's well combined.

== Adding the Greens ==

Add the pak choi to your soup.

Stir and cook until pak choi is tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Finishing the Soup ==

Once the pak choi is cooked, add the cooked noodles and broccoli to the soup.

Bring up to the boil again, then immediately remove from the heat.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick - you want a soupy consistency!

Stir in the @soy sauce{25%ml} and squeeze in some lime juice from a lime wedge.

Taste and add more salt, sugar and lime juice if needed.

== Serving ==

Share the prawn noodle soup between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the peanuts and lime zest to finish.

Garnish with any remaining lime wedges. Enjoy!